Flexbox Crash Course 2022
from 0.01
https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=3YW65K6LcIA

two files index.html style.css
create boilerplate
give title
bring in css with link tag
in body Hello World
open Live Server

Use Emmet shortcuts
need a div with class
.flex-container

need items
.item*3{Item $}

style css

create universal selector
box-sizing: border-box
margin: 0			so just creating a reset to 0
padding: 0			so just creating a reset to 0

body font-family use Arial

lets style the items and turn into boxes (easier to show examples this way)

so now we have 3 boxes
add details to the class .flex-container
remember to create flex container need to add display property and set to flex for flex row
add background light grey to see better

now show life before flex blox
comment out display flex
now add float onto the item itself BUT if add h3 Hello after div closed 
then that Hello is also part of the float (NOT WHAT WE WANT)
so to FIX Hello sitting as part of the float we would need to add
.flex-container::after {
	content: '';
	clear: both;
	display: block;
}
and this then puts Hello on line below 3 items.
But in addition to adding this extra code, we didnt have access to any of the flex properties.
so lets go back to display flex code
delete html Hello line
delete .flex-container::after
un-comment display: flex line inside .flex-container block

video 9.52 of 46.53

get into very helpful alignment properties now
use on the .flex-container and not on the items

explain justify-content horizontally
explain justify-content vertically
explain just 1 of 3 boxes 			video 12.30 of 46.53


